GG_X_RUSH AND X_RUSH
by dustandechoes89

=====================================================================
X_rush is a fairly large map with many hidden weapons. There is a scout on top 
of the covered bridge, smoke and HE grenades on the cornered balconies, an m4 in the 
T-spawn vent, and an AK in the CT-spawn vent. To retrieve the vent weapons, simply
buy a nade, and toss it in the vent (it works best if you hit the very top of the slanted
piece). Have fun!
=====================================================================
The only difference between the maps is the "gg" map (Gungame, of course) 
has the buyzones and weapons taken out, as well as the vent.
=====================================================================
Feel free to send comments and/or suggestions to arekuthelastspartan@hotmail.com

xmas_tree_jumping Bouncing / Jumping / scoutsknifes / surf / ultimate xmas fun!!! This map combines xmas and diferent game modes in CSS to create an ultimatly fun and jumping time. Each team cut their own spawns into the tree and are getting ready to bounce across the side of it. If you fall you will bounce back up again to rejoin your team in the ultimate fight. I wanted to create this map for a diferent look into mapping and making something that everyone can get some fun out of. Thanks for everyone that helped me create this and let me use things like textures. Note: this is only a first beta version. Your feedback will be used to make the map better for everyone. I hope you love playing this map as much as I have making. Thanks, drimp. (video to come) Things to do: - add more detail and better brushwork. - use peoples feedback to make it better. - get better lighting and custom skybox. - change some textures. - try to somehow create a nav. - add fpsb logo. - upgrade 3dskybox. - other things.

This is a map that will work in regualr CS:S, but it is meant for 4HM's Gun Game Mod. It is a very fast paced map. I beta tested it with the WTF clan from theserverspot.com and everyone seemed to enjoy it. The people that like it loved it and those that complained... well lets just say they were the ones that were -12-20. The fans push you up to the next level and I have fixed them so they dont push you too high. You can also jump from the top level onto the fan of the bottom level and coast down to the bottom floor slowly. Everyones FPS ran from 50-70 and I have since done some optimizing which boosted the fps by 15-30. Hope everyone enjoys this map and if there are any bugs you find PM me. Look for the release of my next map wtf_toohigh which utilizes a new combination of triggers that so far though beta testing has lead to some awsome game play.

---- Introduction ----

In "Worms Explorium", multiple entities, special effects and movement modifiers are put on interactive display for the counter-strike:source players and map makers.

Worms Explorium is layed out like a hands-on museum with three separate areas:  Special Effects, Movement Modifiers and Things to Shoot.  The goal of this map is provide a way for CSS map makers to interact wih various unique visual a motor
functions on a map and then be able to dissect and relate those functions to their sources in the VMF file.  As such, both the BSP and VMF files are included within the distribution ZIP.

Note that some of the effects can be disabled or changed by settings within the player's configuration file.  If certain effects, like rain and snow, are not visibile - check to make sure that they are not disabled in the configuration file.  The map uses only standard textures and effects except for the "Worms Explorium" decal.

I tried to make the implementations as basic as possible.  As such, sound is limited to whatever capability a particular entity may offer or, for certain other effects, provided by ambient_generic entities.  I did not implement any sound environments (which is why the rain is silent).

Some of the effects can be replayed by a push of a button while others, especially in the Things to Shoot area, which get destroyed are one-time shows.

Also, there are probably dozens of ways to implement the effects in the Explorium.  I have used configurations and settings which I used in various maps and which seemed to, at least, work.

I hope this compilation helps mappers with implementations and possibly to strike a spark of inspiration for some new map or map effects.

This is a remake of hang em high. I'm NOT the original mapper, though I did make a lot of changes. I took a decompiled version, retextured and revamped it.  I've added many platforms, added teleporters, added 2 bomb sites (making it a bomb/defuse map), removed all the weapon pickups and added buy zones. Additional credit goes to Cyber for some of the layout ideas.  Good for regular gameplay or WCS mod.

This is a remake of de_dolls, a rats styled map. The errors were removed (if you're familiar with the original you know what I mean), some very minor tweaking was done, but mostly this is a retexture. I completely remade the pillow on the bed, added some necessary player clip brushes (although invisible they help you not get caught on corners, etc.) and even added a popcorn container. :) All the new textures are custom made & colored by me (though I didn't necessarily create the image files from scratch on all of them, obviously). Good for regular or WCS mod.
